Tis the Season of Giving🎄…FULL CIRCLE MOMENT ⭕️ …. 
Before becoming a full time artist/ influencer I was a k-12 music teacher for 10 years…What an amazing time it was but in some cases we didn’t always have the financial resources to expose the kiddos to outside performances beyond the classroom.
…  I would literally turn the music room into a pretend concert hall.. just to give them an opportunity to see  shows and experience the wonderful world of the arts…I always hoped after retiring from teaching I would be able to help students experience the performing arts. 

This year I teamed up with @avondaledealerships 
and their #7daysofgiving initiative to make an impact on the community and give back to a cause or charity of my choice. After much thought and reflection I knew @broadwaydallas Give a Kid a Seat Program was the perfect opportunity to make a major impact for children in the arts. 
This amazing organization gives the chance for students to experiment the Magic of Broadway shows and experience STEM educational programming.  Im honored to give back to this program 

Thank you so much @avondaledealerships for choosing me to partner on this 4th day of your 7 days of giving program and letting me give the ultimate Golden Ticket  to something so true and special to
My heart… and of course thank you for letting me spread holiday cheer with grace and style in my dream car the fabulous @porsche Cayenne SUV.  What a wow wonderful moment.

#7daysofgiving #giveback #avondaleselect

#EVENTDUMP ❤️…#sponsored ….This has truly been Madelyn’s Magic month.. My BIRTHDAY is still going and I have been having so much FUN. 

There have some really great experiences to share… but I have to thank @hellonewhouse and the Cast of “Magic Mike LIVE” @mmltour for having me to experience a VIP viewing of the amazing show and being the official kickoff of my bday festivities while on their tour stop in Dallas. 

I wasn’t sure what to expect with the show but it was SOOO good. There was so much artistry and talent that blew me away and  definitely a bit of spice 🌶️😉. We had luxury front row plush couch seating, fabulously curated cocktails brought to us by a private concierge and a private meet in greet with the Cast (See “Magic Mike” in first pic )  it was definitely a fun night to remember.  Grab your girls and go watch this amazing show for a fun girls night out!!

Well, it’s officially World Opera Day.. And I flipped that ish didn’t I?! What is Trap Opera you ask? TRAP (or The Reimagined Artistic Progressive) OPERA. 😍

It’s in your face, bold, flavorful gritty and is a sound that’s not meant to back down, but to stand up and be fierce. It’s been amazing to present you all with contemporary storytelling for the modern ear and I’m so excited to share what’s next! Until then here are some of my favorite TRAP OPERA moments 🤭💋🎵🎶 #trapopera #innovation

When you’re attending the grand opening of @fogo and the CEO of the company ends up asking you to serenade the VIP members. I happily obliged. 😉😉🎬🥰

I want to say a huge thank you to  the team of @fogo for having us for a beautiful evening! More pics of the experience coming soon

BRAVO…..Girls night at the Opera was a blast ❤️❤️. We had so much fun in the Arts District we had to make a part on and 2 recap of our fabulous evening.  Thank you @thedallasopera for a wonderful time last Thursday to see the world Premier of “The Diving Bell and the Butterly” 

This was such a fabulous night complete with a pre- cocktail hour, intermission lounge, orchestra seating and off course  beautiful music.  My guest and I had such a wonderful time and left enriched from this contemporary work composed by  Joby Talbot.  If you are looking for an opulent outing in Dallas  with the  girls, consider a show during their current season.  I’ve linked Info on all of their upcoming shows in my story.  Bravissima 💋💋💋
